Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Companion to SDL-side patch 0024. When DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG env var is set (e.g.
"R1"), the engine writes to "<TAG>.LOG" instead of "debug.log". Path
resolution still goes through ResourceManager::getPrefPath so the file lands
at the same prefdir (game directory on DOS = C:\DOSKUTSU\).

Together patches 0024 + 0069 let the wave-13.6.1 keyboard-regression bisect
use trivial .bat files: each .bat SETs DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG=R{N} along with the
config-specific RING_CHUNKS / FORCE_PUMP_YIELD vars, runs DOSKUTSU.EXE, and
that's it — logs land directly at R{N}.LOG and R{N}SDL.LOG, no rename
needed, no freeze edge case where logs get clobbered on the next launch.

Slot was originally tentatively reserved for wave 14 (decouple engine tick)
per docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §6; wave 14 renumbers to 0070.

See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §2 for the wave 13.6.1 bisect design.
---
 src/main.cpp | 13 ++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index 5f091ae..49ae2d4 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -353,7 +353,18 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
   std::freopen("NUL", "w", stderr);
 #endif
 
-  Logger::init(ResourceManager::getInstance()->getPrefPath("debug.log"));
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0069, Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): the log-file basename is
+  // overridable via the DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG env var so a multi-config bisect can
+  // write each run's engine log to a unique filename without renames. When
+  // unset, default "debug.log" is used. When set to e.g. "R1", logs go to
+  // "R1.LOG" (uppercase per DOS convention). Pairs with SDL-side patch 0024
+  // which uses the same env var for "/<TAG>SDL.LOG".
+  std::string _log_basename = "debug.log";
+  const char *_log_tag = std::getenv("DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG");
+  if (_log_tag && _log_tag[0] != '\0') {
+    _log_basename = std::string(_log_tag) + ".LOG";
+  }
+  Logger::init(ResourceManager::getInstance()->getPrefPath(_log_basename));
 //  SDL_LogSetAllPriority(SDL_LOG_PRIORITY_VERBOSE);
 
 #ifdef NXE_DOS
